did.abstract: The Muhlenberg, Kentucky glass plate negatives (dated 1929; 0.88 cubic feet; 5 boxes) consist of 149 glass plate negatives of high school and family photographs taken in Muhlenberg, Kentucky during the 1920s and 1930s.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open to researchers by appointment.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: 2021av022: [identification of item], Muhlenberg, Kentucky glass plate negatives, 1929, University of Kentucky Libraries Special Collections Research Center.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Muhlenberg, Kentucky glass plate negatives (dated 1929; 0.88 cubic feet; 5 boxes) consist of 149 glass plate negatives of high school and family photographs taken in Muhlenberg, Kentucky during the 1920s and 1930s.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The physical rights to the materials in this collection are held by the University of Kentucky Libraries Special Collections Research Center.
